HIV/AIDS: Cutar ta ƙaru da kashi 14% a China
China ta ce adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV da kuma cutar kanjamau a kasar ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Ma'aikatan sun ce akwai fiye da mutane 820,000 da ke fama da cutar a ƙasar.
An sake gano cutar a cikin mutane 40,000 a ƙarshen 2018.
Sun lura cewa mutane sun kamu da cutar ta wurin jima'i, kuma wannan canji ne sosai daga yadda suke a dā.
A gaskiya ma, an yaɗa cutar HIV ta hanyar ƙarin jini a wasu biranen ƙasar Sin.
A wani taron da aka yi a birnin Yunnan, ƙasar Sin ta ce cutar ba ta sake yaɗuwa ba.
Amma, ana sa ran cewa adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV da kuma cutar Aids zai ƙaru zuwa 100,000 a kowace shekara.
A ƙasar Sin, yawan kamuwa da cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i ya fi yawa tsakanin mutanen da suke da jima'i da juna.
A shekarar 1997, kasar Sin ta amince da luwadi, amma adawa da luwadi a cikin al'umma ta zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Amma, domin yanayin al'umma, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90% na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna aurar da mata.
Ƙari ga haka, ana samun cututtuka ta wajen yin jima'i da ba a shirya ba a irin wannan hanyar.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin ba da taimako na jin dadi kyauta ga masu cutar HIV a matsayin mataki na gwamnati na magance matsalar.
